%N A060746 Absolute value of numerator of non-Euler-constant term of Laurent expansion of Gamma function at s = -n.
%C A060746 If you start with log(z) and integrate it n times in succession, then you get z^n*log(z)/n! - K(n)*z^n where K(1)=1, K(2)=3/4, K(3)=11/36, K(4)=25/288, K(5)=137/7200, K(6)=49/14400, etc. - _Warren D. Smith_, Jan 01 2006
%C A060746 The coefficients in the expansion of the n-th integral of log(x)^m were discussed in Loeb & Rota, 1989 (briefly overviewed in page 12 of Dan Rus, 2025), with Warren D. Smith's comment being the m=1 special case. - _Natalia L. Skirrow_, Jun 07 2026
%H A060746 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A060746/b060746.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A060746 Daniel E Loeb and Gian-Carlo Rota, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0001-8708(89)90079-0">Formal power series of logarithmic type</a>, Advances in Mathematics, 1989, Vol. 75, Iss. 1, pp. 1-118.
%H A060746 Mircea Dan Rus, 2025, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.08762">Yet another note on notation</a>, arXiv:2501.08762 [math.HO], 2025.
%H A060746 Natalia L. Skirrow, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/User:Natalia_L._Skirrow/an_introduction_to_Stirling_numbers/more_on_Faulhabernoulli_and_Gregory#more_log-gamma_series_things">more on Faulhabernoulli and Gregory § more log-gamma series things</a>.
%H A060746 Natalia L. Skirrow, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/User:Natalia_L._Skirrow/above_the_Stirling_triangles#recursive_integrals_of_powers_of_logs">above the Stirling triangles § recursive integrals of powers of logs</a>.
%F A060746 Conjecture: a(n) = lcm(Wolstenholme(n), n!)/n!, cf. A007406. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, May 20 2004
%F A060746 Equivalent conjecture: a(n) = numerator(harmonic(n)/(n-1)!) for n >= 1. - _Peter Luschny_, May 13 2023
%F A060746 Conjecture: for n>=2, a(n) = numerator of H(n)/((n-1)!*H(n-1)) where H(n) is the n-th harmonic number = Sum_{k=1..n} 1/k. - _Gary Detlefs_, Sep 09 2010
%F A060746 From _Natalia L. Skirrow_, Jun 07 2026: (Start)
%F A060746 Both conjectures are true.
%F A060746 Gamma(s+m) = Gamma(m)*(1 + digamma(m)*s + O(s^2)), and digamma(m) = H(m-1) - gamma.
%F A060746 Via Euler's reflection formula,
%F A060746   Gamma(s-n) = (1/Gamma(n+1-s)) / (sin(Pi*(s-n))/Pi)
%F A060746   = ((1 + digamma(n+1)*s + O(s^2))/n!) / ((-1)^n*(s + O(s^3))),
%F A060746   whose constant term is (-1)^n*digamma(n+1)/n!, whose rational part is (-1)^n*H(n)/n!, so a(n) = num(H(n)/n!) (Vladeta Jovovic's).
%F A060746 Let num(x) = numerator of x. Writing H(n) = p/q with p,q coprime, H(n)/H(n-1) = p*n/(p*n-q), so num(H(n)/H(n-1)) / num(H(n)) = n/gcd(q,p*n) = n/gcd(q,n) = num(n*H(n)) / num(H(n)) = A120263(n). Therefore Gary Detlefs's num(H(n)/((n-1)!*H(n-1))) is num(n*H(n)/(n-1)!), which equals a(n)'s definition since gcd(denominator(H(n)),n) = n.
%F A060746 (End)
%e A060746 series(Gamma(s), s=-4,1 ) = series(1/24*(s+4)^(-1)+(25/288-1/24*gamma)+O((s+4)),s=-4,1). Hence a(4)=25.
%e A060746 series(Gamma(s), s=-5,1 ) = series(-1/120*(s+5)^(-1)+(-137/7200+1/120*gamma)+O((s+5)),s=-5,1). Hence a(5)=137.
%t A060746 A060746[n_] := Numerator[HarmonicNumber[n]/(n-1)!];
%t A060746 Array[A060746, 35, 0] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 12 2026 *)
%o A060746 (Python)
%o A060746 from math import gcd
%o A060746 def a_gen():
%o A060746     yield 0
%o A060746     yield 1
%o A060746     a0 = 0; a1 = 1; n = 2
%o A060746     f = 4; z = 1; m = 1; k = 3
%o A060746     while True:
%o A060746         s = -k * a1 - m * a0
%o A060746         a0, a1 = a1, s
%o A060746         m = n * n; f *= m;
%o A060746         k += 2; n += 1; z = -z
%o A060746         yield z * s // gcd(s, f)
%o A060746 a = a_gen(); print([next(a) for _ in range(31)])  # _Peter Luschny_, Jun 08 2026
